    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="976"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d976">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/174</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-16">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">No. 315]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note No. 315 of yesterday’s
                        date<note n="2" xml:id="d976fn2">Not printed.</note> respecting large
                    cargoes of coal being taken on board German ships in United States ports, I have
                    the honour to bring to your notice that the <hi rend="italic">Vaterland</hi>
                    which is in readiness to sail from New York Harbour has 17,000 tons of coal on
                    board.</p>
                <p>In calling your attention to the above fact, which clearly indicates that the
                    ship in question is not bent on a peaceful mission, and also in view of the
                    circumstance that there is a strong probability of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Vaterland</hi> being converted into a German armed cruiser on the high
                    seas, I have the honour to request that pending investigation by the United
                    States authorities the vessel may be detained with a view to such action as the
                    United States Government may think right and proper.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
